#Text=Irish rock band The Cranberries ' lead singer Dolores O'Riordan dies at 46
#Text=Thursday , January 18 , 2018

#Text=On Monday , 46-year-old Dolores O'Riordan , lead singer of Irish rock band The Cranberries , was found dead , her publicist Lindsey Holmes confirmed ; reports suggested she was found in her room at the London Hilton on Park Lane hotel .
#Text=O'Riordan 's agent said she was in London , England , for a recording session .
#Text=According to the police , her death was considered " unexplained " and no cause of death disclosed , though it was to be investigated .
#Text=File photo of Dolores O'Riordan
#Text=Image : Eva Rinaldi .
#Text=( Reuseterms . )
#Text=Later one of the richest women of Ireland , O'Riordan joined the rock band , then known as " the Cranberry Saw Us " , as a teenager around 1989 , after Niall Quinn had left the band .
#Text=Also featuring drummer Fergal Lawler , bassist Mike Hogan and his brother Noel Hogan , the lead guitarist , the band released their first album Everybody Else Is Doing It , So Why Ca n't We ?
#Text=in 1993 .
#Text=The debut album featuring single Linger was an international success .
#Text=The band went on to release six more albums featuring O'Riordan 's voice , including Something Else , which was released last year .
#Text=A year later , in 1994 , the band released their second studio album , No Need to Argue , which featured the song Zombie , a song about bombings related to Northern Ireland .
#Text=Zombie topped the singles charts in various countries .
#Text=In the same year , O'Riordan married Don Burton , sometime manager of the Duran Duran band .
#Text=Their third album , To the Faithful Departed , was released in 1996 .
#Text=The album did not receive the acclamation of the first two .
#Text=In 2003 , the band split , and it was reunited in 2009 .
#Text=During those six years , O'Riordan released two solo albums — Are You Listening ?
#Text=in 2007 and No Baggage in 2009 .
#Text=2012 's Roses was the first album The Cranberries released after reunification .
#Text=Last year , O'Riordan revealed through London 's Metro newspaper she had been diagnosed with bipolar disorder .
#Text=She also spoke of suffering from depression to The Irish News .
#Text=In 2014 , the singer was involved in assaulting a flight attendant and three police officials on a flight from New York , US to Ireland .
#Text=She was fined € 6000 ( US$ 6600 ) after she pleaded guilty ; medical reports said she suffered from mental illness during that incident .
#Text=Last year , the band 's tour to North America and Europe for Something Else was cancelled partway through as O'Riordan suffered from a back problem .
#Text=After announcement of O'Riordan 's death , Irish prime minister Leo Varadkar tweeted , " For anyone who grew up in Ireland in the 1990s , Dolores O'Riordan was the voice of a generation .
